cs.CV, cs.MM, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.GR 

This paper proposes a deep learning-based approach for image and video denoising, which falls under the computer vision (cs.CV) and multimedia (cs.MM) sub-categories. The use of deformable kernels involves learning the sampling locations and kernel weights, which is a machine learning task and falls under the machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. The paper also discusses the use of trilinear sampling and regularization, which are graphics-related techniques and fall under the graphics (cs.GR) sub-category.
